The paper discusses the challenge of constructing and maintaining machine learning models over large, multi-dimensional, and evolving data, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on Bayesian networks, which are a type of graphical model commonly used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper also discusses the need to scale to distributed, streaming data, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases). 

The paper proposes a communication-efficient method for learning and maintaining the Bayesian network model, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
